If the MTR is adopted, the bill goes back to the committee for further debate. 

This Congress, Republicans have won 2 MTR votes - something Democrats were never able to accomplish in their last 8 years as the minority.

Democrats are frantically trying to think of new ways to silence Republicans.

In the House, 1 of the most powerful tools the minority party can use is the motion to recommit (MTR), meaning anyone in the chamber can challenge a bill being brought to the floor by requesting a MTR.
